HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 577
By Cochran
A RESOLUTION to honor Coach Johnny Morgan on the occasion
of his retirement.
WHEREAS, the members of the General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to one of the greatest high school basketball coaches of all time who has coached his teams to
more than a thousand victories over his forty-seven-year career at Central High School of
McMinn County; and
WHEREAS, for almost five decades, Coach Johnny Morgan has been the heart and soul
of Central High School of McMinn County's girls' basketball program and guided the
Chargerettes to unprecedented heights of achievement; and
WHEREAS, Coach Morgan recently announced his retirement after amassing a record
of 1,107-397; he became only the third girls' basketball coach in TSSAA history to win 1,000
games when he reached that amazing total in 2022; and
WHEREAS, during his forty-seven years as head coach of the girls' basketball program,
Johnny Morgan led Central to the school's first state championship in 2011 and seventeen trips
to the state tournament, finishing runner-up in 1997, 2004, 2010, 2015, and 2023; and
WHEREAS, during his illustrious career, the Chargerettes have won twenty-two district
tournament championships, twenty-two region tournament championships, and seventeen
sectional wins, with twenty of the district tournament and twenty-one of the region tournament
wins coming since 1997; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of his extraordinary achievements as a coach in Tennessee
high school athletics, Johnny Morgan was inducted into the TSSAA Hall of Fame in 2012; and
WHEREAS, over the course of forty-seven years, Johnny Morgan has earned the
respect and admiration of his colleagues and sports fans across the State as a great basketball
